    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a driver-focused 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at an 8,400 RPM redline. The 6-speed manual gearbox provides short, precise throws, paired with a variable M-differential lock for optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including a rod bearing service using VAC coated bearings and replacement of the throttle actuators. The chassis retains its composure via Electronic Damper Control (EDC), and the hydraulic steering rack offers the communicative feedback lost in later generations. While the Alpine White exterior shows minor stone chips consistent with spirited use, the mechanical vitals are robust, the subframe is intact, and the oil analysis reports remain clean.",
      "price": 33500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
